### Description

When doing SSR and having too many API calls on the server side, the transfer state will get bigger and bigger and that whole information adds up to size and the initial html document gets very large. 

By having some json minifying algorithm in place we can shrink that down in a great way. 

Currently the only way to have this is to hack into TransferState and patch the store field and toJson field. (the onSerialize method is good, but it only helps per key instead of the whole json). 

```ts
// hack-y way
provideEnvironmentInitializer(() => {
            const transferState = inject(TransferState);
            const jsonMinifier = inject(JsonMinifier);
            const platform = inject(PLATFORM);
            if (platform.isServerRendered) {
                // @ts-ignore
                transferState['store'] = jsonMinifier.onRestore(transferState['store']);
            } else if (platform.isServer) {
                transferState.toJson = (): string => {
                     // @ts-ignore
                    returnJSON.stringify(jsonMinifier.onSerialize(transferState['store']));
                };
            }
        }),
```

### Proposed solution

Having a way to hook into json retrieval from html and json serialization would be great. 

### Alternatives considered

Keep the hack in place.

